article.description: Kerem Kanter scored 19 points and pulled down 11 rebounds as Green Bay drubbed Division III St. Mary's (MN) 108-59 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Kanter has 19 points, Green Bay blows by St. Mary's (MN)
article.linkText: Kanter has 19 points, Green Bay blows by St. Mary's (MN)
article.story: ASHWAUBENON, Wis. -- Kerem Kanter scored 19 points and pulled down 11 rebounds as Green Bay drubbed Division III St. Mary's (MN) 108-59 on Thursday night. Kanter hit 5 of 8 field goals and made 9 of 12 free throws. Jamar Hurdle came off the bench to knock down 10 of 14 from the floor for 21 points. Warren Jones added 13. Kameron Hankerson and David Jesperson chipped in 10 points apiece for Green Bay (6-6) as all 10 players put points on the board. Tevin Findlay broke the school record for steals in a game, picking off nine as the Phoenix tied the team record with 22 steals. Findlay also dished out seven assists. Green Bay, which jumped out to a 23-8 lead, recorded a season-high 53 points in the first half, leading 53-31 at the break. The Phoenix, who never trailed, won the second half 55-28. James Cullen led St. Mary's with nine points.
